All interns in the pilot program shall be governed by the provisions of KRS 161.030, except requirements specified in subsections (5), (6), (7), and (9) of KRS 161.030 which the board may deem inappropriate to the pilot program and which shall be modified in administrative regulations promulgated by the board. The board shall promulgate administrative regulations that specify:
Conditions under which prospective intern candidates shall be chosen for participation;
Incentives to encourage participation in the two (2) year pilot program;
Responsibilities of the beginning teacher committee;
Duties of teacher mentors;
Certification options for interns who may leave the pilot program or lose employment during the pilot years or who have not successfully completed the internship within the two (2) year period;
Time, content, and assessment requirements during the mentoring and assessment phases of the internship period; and
Other provisions necessary to implement the pilot program.
